1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a novel protocol for efficient information transmission and energy transfer in a wireless-powered relay system. The optimal power allocation and beamforming design are also derived, which are typical topics in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper studies a wireless-powered relay system, which is a typical networking scenario. The proposed protocol aims to improve the throughput of the system, which is a common goal in networking research.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new protocol for energy and information transmission in a relay system, which involves control and optimization of the system. The optimal power allocation and beamforming design are also derived, which are typical topics in control theory.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper studies a wireless relay system that can transmit multimedia information. The proposed protocol aims to improve the throughput of the system, which is important for multimedia applications.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a new protocol for energy and information transmission in a relay system, which involves optimization and computation of the system. The optimal power allocation and beamforming design are also derived, which are typical topics in computational engineering.
